The hands that feed us. 

I met Alexis many years ago and she made a deep impact on my view of food, patriotism, and most importantly, optimism. I think it’s a quality all farmers have to possess when you’re dealing with how unforgiving nature can be. 

Support your local farms and businesses. And if you find yourself in Napa Valley, reach out to @soulfoodfarm and buy a bottle of her incredible olive oil. Best I’ve had.

Breakfast at PB Clark’s in King, North Carolina.

Everytime I go home to visit, my dad and I eat breakfast here. Western omelet for him and a bowl of buttery grits for me. Lingering here in the mornings while the regular’s fill into their booths and flirt with the waitresses.

Spent two mornings here last month getting to know the stories of the customers who call this place home. Veterans, factory works, farmers, truck drivers. And what an honor it was.

There were a lot of “I’ll be darned!”, “I’m going to break your camera!” “Is LA as dangerous as it is on TV?”

Anyways, thanks for scrolling through.
